The paper proposes a Bayesian nonparametric model for the Hawkes process and presents an EM-variational inference scheme. The paper involves machine learning techniques such as Gaussian processes and variational inference, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with statistical inference and time series analysis, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves information theory and signal processing, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
